  <prompt>
    Author `GetUserPreferencesHandler` (NEW) at `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/GetUserPreferencesHandler.cs` implementing the T4 `get_user_preferences()` tool per architecture §8.1. READ-ONLY: reads from `sprk_userpreferences` Dataverse entity (existing — used by SmartTodo + LegalWorkspace) via `IUserPreferencesService` (architecture §4.4 — verify whether existing service is present; if absent, create a thin read-only service). Returns `{ writingStyle, summaryLength, citationStyle, pinnedPlaybooks[] }`. Implements FR-30 (get_user_preferences row of the 8-tool surface).
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in chat tool-handler authoring + Dataverse `sprk_userpreferences` read patterns.</role>

  <goal>
    `GetUserPreferencesHandler` lives at `Services/Ai/Handlers/GetUserPreferencesHandler.cs` implementing `IToolHandler`. Reads via `IUserPreferencesService` (existing if SmartTodo registered it; else new at `Services/Ai/Memory/UserPreferencesService.cs`). Returns the §8.1 user-preferences shape verbatim. Returns sensible defaults (`writingStyle: "concise" | summaryLength: "medium" | citationStyle: "inline" | pinnedPlaybooks: []`) on read failure per architecture §9.1 graceful-degradation. Single `ToolResult`; tier-1-safe telemetry; ≤+0.1 MB delta. Unit tests cover hit, defaults-on-failure, ADR-015 telemetry safety.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per architecture §3.1 (T4) + §4.4 (UserPreferencesService — verify or create) + §4.3 (existing R6/SmartTodo components reused) + §8.1 schema + §8.2 routing (always-on). T4 is bound by ADR-013 facade — chat code READS via this handler; WRITES go through user-settings UI (out of scope here).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/ManagePinnedContextHandler.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Memory/PinnedContextRepository.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">No new endpoint.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Auto-discovered; `IUserPreferencesService` (existing or new) is registered by task 091.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">T4 is bound by facade — but this handler is READ-ONLY from chat side; the service it consumes (`IUserPreferencesService`) wraps the Dataverse read. NO direct `IDataverseClient` injection into the handler.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Telemetry payload: handlerName + sessionId + userId (boolean present/absent) + decision (`hit` | `defaults`) + durationMs ONLY. NEVER preference values.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">≤+0.1 MB delta (read-only wrapper).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">SINGLE `ToolResult` return.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture">§3.2 rule 3 — T4 bound by ADR-013 facade; chat reads via `get_user_preferences`; writes go through user-settings UI (out of scope here).</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture">§9.1 — graceful degradation on `sprk_userpreferences` read failure: return defaults; log Warning.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/architecture/stateful-chat-architecture.md</file>
