  <steps>
    <step order="1">Load architecture §3.1, §4.3, §4.4, §8.1, §9.1.</step>
    <step order="2">Grep across `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` for `UserPreferencesService` to confirm presence; if absent, plan to author a minimal read-only `Services/Ai/Memory/UserPreferencesService.cs` + interface that wraps the Dataverse `sprk_userpreferences` read.</step>
    <step order="3">Author `Services/Ai/Handlers/GetUserPreferencesHandler.cs` implementing `IToolHandler`. No parameters required.</step>
    <step order="4">Implement `ExecuteAsync`: call `IUserPreferencesService.GetAsync(tenantId, userId, ct)`; on success map to §8.1 shape; on failure return defaults `{ writingStyle: "concise", summaryLength: "medium", citationStyle: "inline", pinnedPlaybooks: [] }` and log Warning per §9.1.</step>
    <step order="5">If `IUserPreferencesService` does not exist: create it at `Services/Ai/Memory/UserPreferencesService.cs` + `IUserPreferencesService.cs`. Inject the existing Dataverse read client used by SmartTodo's `sprk_userpreferences` consumers.</step>
    <step order="6">Add Dataverse seed-row JSON at `infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-get-user-preferences-row.json`.</step>
    <step order="7">Author unit tests: hit, defaults-on-failure, ADR-015 telemetry safety.</step>
    <step order="8">Run `dotnet build` + `dotnet test`. Must pass.</step>
    <step order="9">Measure BFF publish-size delta; write `notes/handoffs/089-bff-publish-delta.md`.</step>
    <step order="10">Run code-review + adr-check (Step 9.5).</step>
    <step order="11">Update TASK-INDEX.md: 089 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Reference handlers + architecture</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Locate existing UserPreferencesService</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Handler + (possibly) service + tests + seed-row JSON</tool>
